[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-14T20:32:07+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Asus ROG Zephyrus Duo 15 half open from the back.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TQTP9N-T2otqgYN5JF883chTNqo=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73408699/mchin_181204_4182_0006.0.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Monica Chin / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"TW8q8B\">Asus\u2019 reputation for customer support has been tarnished, and the company is now pledging a long list of concrete fixes <a href=\"https://gamersnexus.net/news-features/confronting-asus-face-face\">to <em>Gamers Nexus</em></a><em>.</em> Chief among them: if you\u2019ve ever been denied a warranty repair or charged for a service that was unnecessary or should\u2019ve been free, Asus wants to hear from you at a new email address. It claims those disputes will be processed by Asus\u2019 own staff rather than outsourced customer support agents.</p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><aside id=\"xV6Ezq\"><div></div></aside></div>\n<p id=\"wRCyxR\">And, after <a", "id": 715315, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/14/24178785/asus-customer-support-gamers-nexus", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How Asus is overhauling its customer support after Gamers Nexus investigation", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-14T20:17:46+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A 3D version of the Yacht Club Games logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5O2hz3HAfWKJxM9SnAWwS8YyO_w=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73408667/videoframe_1517220.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>I wonder what this 3D logo could mean...</em> | Image: Yacht Club Games</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"aCjhU6\">Shovel Knight might be bouncing into 3D. Developer Yacht Club Games just announced a new mainline game in the hit series that started as a retro-inspired 2D platformer, and the studio says this new game will \u201claunch Shovel Knight into an entirely new dimension of gaming,\u201d <a href=\"https://www.yachtclubgames.com/blog/what-s-next-for-shovel-knight/\">according to a blog post</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"42x2gi\">If that wasn\u2019t enough of a clue about the move to 3D, the Yacht Club Games\u2019 Friday livestream celebrating the 10th anniversary of <em>Shovel Knight</em> featured an even more pointed hint: a 3D version of the Yacht Clu", "id": 715316, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/14/24178773/shovel-knight-sequel-new-dimension-3d", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Shovel Knight is getting a sequel in a \u2018new dimension\u2019", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-14T19:59:53+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Phones from Google, Apple, and Samsung on a colorful illustrated background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/t2Mje1exJnZyEZRBhf5hrBEQbvE=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/67732462/226422_K_Radtke_budget_phone_buying_guide.13.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>You can get a great device for less than $500 these days if you know how to pick your priorities.</em> | Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>You can\u2019t have everything at this price, but you can get a great smartphone. Whether you want an iPhone, a 120Hz screen, or water resistance, you\u2019ve got options.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/21420196/best-budget-smartphone-cheap\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 715317, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/21420196/best-budget-smartphone-cheap", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The best smartphone you can buy for under $500", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-14T19:29:59+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the Apple logo in the EU stars.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/LskZP77kFzaGVsDl9kJAbjEj6yA=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73408584/STK450_EU_G.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"BqU6lf\">Apple and Meta could soon face charges from the European Commission for violating Digital Markets Act (DMA) rules. The <a href=\"https://www.ft.com/content/31a996d5-b472-4357-953e-ace078494604\"><em>Financial Times</em> reported Friday</a> that the Commission is planning to charge Apple, and <a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/technology/apple-meta-set-face-eu-charges-under-landmark-tech-rules-sources-say-2024-06-14/\"><em>Reuters</em> reported later</a> that Meta could be charged as well.</p>\n<p id=\"gcXkCG\">The Commission is reported to be targeting Apple over its \u201csteering\u201d rules that charge developers for pointing to third-party purchase options. Meta\u2019s char", "id": 714959, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/14/24178724/apple-meta-eu-charges-dma", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple and Meta could face charges for violating EU tech rules", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-14T18:17:34+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"DJI Mini 3 drone and remote sitting on rocks\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Phgi1jTFO-UdBsVftd9y-Tt03Ng=/1705x562:5706x3229/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73408474/DJI_Mini_3___Outdoor_KV_Standalone__with_RC_N1_.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>You can do a lot with this little combo.</em> | Image: DJI</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"VuojLw\">Drones aren\u2019t just fun to fly \u2014 they\u2019ve also become nearly mandatory in creative arsenals to satisfy clients and social media followers hungering for aerial photography and video. Thankfully, the entry-level price barrier has come crashing down over the years.</p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><aside id=\"csl9qS\"><div></div></aside></div>\n<p id=\"Ux7zP0\">The previous-generation <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/12/9/23501450/dji-mini-3-drone-announcement-price-date\">DJI Mini 3</a>, for example, is now just $329 ($90 off) at <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/DJI-Mini-RC-Lightweigh", "id": 714665, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/14/24178604/dji-mini-3-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The DJI Mini 3 is only $329 right now, its best price yet", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-14T18:05:24+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Top-down shot of SteelSeries Prime gaming mouse.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/j0JoCf4sGyTE6ddbSEvPzasdfSc=/0x0:2550x1700/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73408431/236715_Best_gaming_mouse_AKrales_0123.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Simple devices can simulate the movements of a computer mouse, but employers are starting to catch on.</em> | Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"AZK9YY\">According to a <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-06-13/wells-fires-over-a-dozen-for-simulation-of-keyboard-activity\">report from <em>Bloomberg</em></a> based on \u201cdisclosures filed with the <a href=\"https://www.finra.org\">Financial Industry Regulatory Authority</a>,\u201d last month, Wells Fargo fired \u201cmore than a dozen employees\u201d after an investigation revealed they were using devices or apps to simulate productivity on their computers. What\u2019s not known is how over a dozen staffers had jobs w", "id": 714666, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/14/24178582/remote-work-mouse-jiggler-mover-wellsfargo", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Remote workers using \u2018mouse-mover\u2019 technology are getting caught", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-14T17:56:55+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Image of Meta\u2019s wordmark on a red background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/hcBLGotXSTGXWAPZ4ONpB9m1Y9I=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73408385/STK043_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_6_Meta.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"MRBljT\">Meta is putting plans for its <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/18/24133808/meta-ai-assistant-llama-3-chatgpt-openai-rival\">AI assistant</a> on hold in Europe after receiving objections from Ireland\u2019s privacy regulator, the company <a href=\"https://about.fb.com/news/2024/06/building-ai-technology-for-europeans-in-a-transparent-and-responsible-way/\">announced on Friday</a>. </p>\n<p id=\"SUqI71\">In a blog post, Meta said the Irish Data Protection Commission (DPC) asked the company to delay training its large language models on content that had been publicly posted to Facebook and Instagram profiles.</p>\n<p id=\"3K2hkt\">Meta said", "id": 714667, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/14/24178591/meta-ai-assistant-europe-ireland-privacy-objections", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Meta says European regulators are ruining its AI bot", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-14T17:06:31+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of the Apple TV 4K set on top of a brown wooden surface.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/qkEMPKpzCL1TOH5Z-IH4hPHw3t4=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73408198/DSCF3862_2.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>With iOS 18, Apple Home users will finally be able to insist the smart home platform use their hardwired Apple TVs as the primary Home hub.</em> | Photo by Chris Welch / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"BlemLu\">While Apple <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24172054/apple-home-homekit-robot-vacuum-support-smart-locks-wwdc24\">barely mentioned</a> its smart home platform during its WWDC 2024 keynote this week, Apple Home users can still rejoice over an update discovered in the first iOS 18 beta: they\u2019re getting the option to choose a \u201cPreferred Home Hub.\u201d This fixes the problem of your smart home \u201cdeciding\u201d to run over Wi-Fi through a HomePod when there\u2019s a perfectly good Apple TV using ether", "id": 714216, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/14/24178482/apple-home-ios18-preferred-home-hub", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple gives Apple Home users something they\u2019ve been begging for", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-14T16:53:17+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo illustration of Elon Musk surrounded by raining dollar bills.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/29Jq7M0jtK4lLDAEES4usT0Y5nU=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73408164/STK022_ELON_MUSK_CVIRGINIA_E.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge, Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"1pRZS4\">I generally find Elon Musk useful, in that he makes it clear which things in America are actually hard boundaries (<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23026874/elon-musk-twitter-buyout-news-updates\">contract law</a>, maybe <a href=\"https://news.bloomberglaw.com/ip-law/x-platform-escapes-most-of-copyright-suit-from-music-publishers\">copyright law</a>) and which are merely conventions (most everything else). You can <a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/business/elon-musk-illegal-drugs-e826a9e1\">take ketamine</a>, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2018/9/7/17830810/elon-musk-smokes-weed-electric-plane-design-joe-rogan", "id": 714217, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/14/24178617/musk-tesla-pay-shareholder-vote", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Whatever Elon wants, Tesla gets", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-14T16:47:16+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of a man wearing a white headband and a red shirt. The man\u2019s holding up a large, gleaming sashimi knife.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/v7gAi1s429lhF9rvffDw1Vo4AQk=/311x0:2804x1662/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73408148/Screenshot_2024_06_14_at_11.43.11_AM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Vertigo / Langdon Foss, Jos\u00e9 Villarrubia, Dave Stewart</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"1TJeJI\">In addition to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/14/24178402/shoujo-clark-kent-and-his-pals-are-coming-back-for-more-adventures-with-superman\">another season</a> of the DC Comics-inspired <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23786075/my-adventures-with-superman-review-adult-swim\"><em>My Adventures with Superman</em></a><em> </em>series, Adult Swim is producing a new animated show based on Vertigo Comics\u2019 <em>Get Jiro! </em>graphic novels by co-writers <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/7/15/22578707/anthony-bourdain-docum", "id": 714218, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24178567/adult-swim-get-jiro-anthony-bourdain-super-mutant-magic-academy", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Anthony Bourdain\u2019s Get Jiro! comic is getting an animated adaptation", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-14T16:33:46+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing what appears to be a prototype of the Galaxy Z Fold 6\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/z82i7-elV1GJ3Jrz1Ew5xWg7DQU=/142x0:3255x2075/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73408111/galaxy_z_fold_6_dummy.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: <a class=\"ql-link\" href=\"https://x.com/UniverseIce/status/1801446432211390695\" target=\"_blank\">Ice Universe</a></figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Q6M4gj\">We already have a sense of potential <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/14/24178341/samsungs-galaxy-z-fold-6-seems-like-a-minor-upgrade\">specs for</a> the Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 6, but now we might have a closer look at the foldable\u2019s design, too. Images <a href=\"https://x.com/UniverseIce/status/1801446432211390695\">shared by reliable leaker Ice Universe</a> show a prototype of the Z Fold 6 with sharper edges and a slight change to its camera design, as <a href=\"https://9to5google.com/2024/06/14/prototype-unit-photos-show-off-galax", "id": 714219, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/14/24178509/samsung-galaxy-z-fold-6-prototype-boxier-design", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 6 prototype points to a squared-off design", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-14T16:30:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Apple\u2019s Craig Federighi presenting Apple\u2019s new Passwords app at WWDC 2024.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kFOwSY31rQ2-6JapBTwUpRTF6lA=/389x0:2438x1366/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73408091/Screenshot_2024_06_14_at_8.58.16_AM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Apple</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"0SC2oM\">Password managers are essential. They keep track of your passwords, encourage better security practices, and generally help to manage your life across your devices. They\u2019re the kind of feature that really should be built into every device \u2014 and Apple is massively expanding their reach with the launch of its new Passwords app, announced this week at WWDC.</p>\n<p id=\"Hykrxb\">We have companies like 1Password and LastPass to thank for the popularity of today\u2019s password managers. But an announcement like Apple\u2019s puts them in a tough position: now that Apple has a free, built-in Passwords app, is there a future for the third-part", "id": 714220, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/14/24178564/apple-password-managers-lastpass-sherlock", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Did Apple just Sherlock our favorite password managers?", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-14T16:11:19+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Three rows of windows on the side of an apartment building with air conditioning units jutting out from several windows. \" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/VC0MynUA5F1_-UhFHm7mCVWu3wg=/0x0:3400x2267/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73408049/1558023909.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Air conditioners in windows during a heat wave in New York, US, on Thursday, July 27, 2023.</em> | Photo: Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"0a18lS\">Household electricity bills could climb with rising temperatures this summer in the US, according to an analysis by the Energy Information Administration (<a href=\"https://www.eia.gov/todayinenergy/detail.php?id=62303#\">EIA</a>). </p>\n<p id=\"OT7Fuo\">Americans\u2019 monthly electricity bills will likely average $173 between June through August, compared to $168 last summer, the EIA predicts. The slight bump in costs comes from consumers cranking up their air conditioning more to cope with a warmer seas", "id": 713704, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/14/24178413/summer-bill-electricity-heat-forecast", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 32, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Your electricity bill is forecast to climb with the summer heat", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-06-14T14:04:46+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing an \u201cadvergame\u201d on a TV\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BZ_-NkLEMOHut6ddlKrStKqfKZ0=/222x0:2286x1376/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73407598/disney_advergames.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Disney\u2019s new \u201cBeat the Block\u201d ad format will let you play golf with your remote.